Uniform Distribution

Set Parameters & Visualize

a <- 0
b <- 1
ggplot() + 
  stat_function(fun = dunif, 
                args = list(a, b))

Sample from the Population

Set the Sample Size
n1 <- 10   # sample size
Simulate Data
data <- tibble(sample = runif(n1, a, b))

ggplot(data, aes(x = sample)) +
  geom_histogram(bins = 20)

Assess Normality
stats <- data %>% 
  summarize(xbar  = mean(sample),
            s     = sd(sample),
            skew  = skewness(sample),
            ekurt = kurtosis(sample) - 3)
stats
# A tibble: 1 × 4
   xbar     s  skew ekurt
  <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl>
1 0.575 0.247 0.238 -1.37
xbar <- stats %>% pull(xbar)
s    <- stats %>% pull(s)

ggplot(data, aes(x = sample)) +
  geom_density() +
  stat_function(fun = dnorm,
                args = list(xbar, s),
                color = "orange",
                size = 1)

ggplot(data, aes(x = sample)) +
  stat_ecdf() +
  stat_function(fun = pnorm,
                args = list(xbar, s),
                color = "orange",
                size = 1)

ggplot(data, aes(sample = sample)) +
  stat_qq() +
  stat_qq_line(color = "orange",
               size = 1)

Distribution of the Sample Mean

Set Sample Size
n2 <- 1   # sample size
Simulate Sample Means
N <- 10^5   # choose number of simulations

simresults <- numeric(N)   # initialize storage vector

for (i in 1:N) {
  simresults[i] <- mean(runif(n2, a, b))
}

data <- tibble(sample = simresults)

ggplot(data, aes(x = sample)) +
  geom_histogram(bins = 20)

Assess Normality
stats <- data %>% 
  summarize(xbar_means  = mean(sample),
            s_means     = sd(sample),
            skew_means  = skewness(sample),
            ekurt_means = kurtosis(sample) - 3)
stats
# A tibble: 1 × 4
  xbar_means s_means skew_means ekurt_means
       <dbl>   <dbl>      <dbl>       <dbl>
1      0.501   0.289   -0.00449       -1.20
xbar_means <- stats %>% pull(xbar_means)
s_means    <- stats %>% pull(s_means)

ggplot(data, aes(x = sample)) +
  geom_density() +
  stat_function(fun = dnorm,
                args = list(xbar_means, s_means),
                color = "orange",
                size = 1)

ggplot(data, aes(x = sample)) +
  stat_ecdf() +
  stat_function(fun = pnorm,
                args = list(xbar_means, s_means),
                color = "orange",
                size = 1)

ggplot(data, aes(sample = sample)) +
  stat_qq() +
  stat_qq_line(color = "orange",
               size = 1)

Distribution of the Sample Mean

Set Sample Size
n2 <- 1   # sample size
Simulate Sample Means
N <- 10^5   # choose number of simulations

simresults <- numeric(N)   # initialize storage vector

for (i in 1:N) {
  simresults[i] <- mean(rexp(n2, lambda))
}

data <- tibble(sample = simresults)

ggplot(data, aes(x = sample)) +
  geom_histogram(bins = 20)

Assess Normality
stats <- data %>% 
  summarize(xbar_means  = mean(sample),
            s_means     = sd(sample),
            skew_means  = skewness(sample),
            ekurt_means = kurtosis(sample) - 3)
stats
# A tibble: 1 × 4
  xbar_means s_means skew_means ekurt_means
       <dbl>   <dbl>      <dbl>       <dbl>
1       1.00    1.00       2.05        6.70

s_means    <- stats %>% pull(s_means)
